# =============================================================================
# renpy — The Ren'Py Visual Novel Engine — Tom Rothamel's open-source
#          engine for creating interactive fiction, visual novels, and
#          life-simulation games.  The Ren'Py engine includes:
#          (1) a complete Python-based runtime that handles graphics
#          (SDL2 + OpenGL), audio (multi-channel mixer, MP3/OGG/WAV),
#          input (keyboard/mouse/gamepad), persistent state, save
#          system, animation, and translation; (2) a custom DSL —
#          THE REN'PY SCRIPTING LANGUAGE — for writing visual novel
#          scripts (`.rpy` files) with character dialogue, scene
#          transitions, branching choices, menus, and image/audio
#          declarations.  Ren'Py's scripting language is GitHub-
#          classified as its own language (lang: "Ren'Py") — a
#          Python-derived DSL with visual-novel-specific syntax
#          (label statements, say statements, menu choices, jump/call,
#          screen language for UI).  Used to ship thousands of
#          published visual novel games — Doki Doki Literature Club
#          (most viral indie VN of 2017, 13M+ downloads), Long Live
#          the Queen, Analogue: A Hate Story, Black Closet, Ladykiller
#          in a Bind, Magical Diary, etc.  Cross-platform: ships
#          Windows, macOS, Linux, Android, iOS, and Web (HTML5).
#
# Author:  Tom Rothamel (@pytom, <pytom@bishoujo.us>) — sole engine
#          author since 2004 (22 years of continuous development);
#          works on Ren'Py full-time funded by Patreon and
#          commercial visual novel licensing.  One of the longest-
#          running single-maintainer game engines actively shipping.
# Source:  https://github.com/renpy/renpy
# CLI:     renpy/arguments.py (custom `ArgumentParser` subclass of
#                                Python stdlib argparse implementing
#                                TWO-PASS parsing: first pass loads
#                                the game and runs init phase
#                                during which Ren'Py games can
#                                REGISTER new commands; second
#                                pass parses sub-commands using the
#                                expanded command registry)
# Library: Python stdlib `argparse` subclass with TWO-PASS dynamic-
#          command-registration extension
#          (Python's argparse is the same Python-stdlib argument-
#           parsing facility that ports to Go via akamensky/argparse
#           R507.  Ren'Py extends it with a two-pass parsing model
#           where commands are REGISTERED DYNAMICALLY by the loaded
#           game during init phase — making argv parsing schema-
#           dependent on which game is being run.)
# License: MIT
# Status:  Active — 6528+ stars on renpy/renpy (created 2012-06-28,
#          continuously developed since 2004 originally on
#          SourceForge; current release Ren'Py 8.3); used in
#          thousands of shipping visual novel commercial titles
#          (full Ren'Py games catalog is impossible to enumerate
