# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY MILESTONE — 69TH DOCUMENTED LANGUAGE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# With this completion the cross-language CLI library taxonomy documents
# its 69TH LANGUAGE — Ren'Py.  Ren'Py joins the corpus as a single-
# instance language (Ren'Py=1) via the `renpy` engine binary using
# a custom subclass of Python stdlib `argparse` with two-pass
# dynamic-command-registration extension.  Taxonomy now spans 284
# cross-language CLI library variants across 69 documented languages.
#
# Leaderboard unchanged: Rust=43 / Go=43 / TS-Node=43 (three-way tie
# at 43 preserved from R544).  Ren'Py=1 (new — 69th language entry).
#
# This is the FIRST documented VISUAL NOVEL ENGINE LANGUAGE in the
# taxonomy.  Every other documented language (general-purpose, DSL
# for parsers/smart-contracts/equations/logic) targets text-based
# programming.  Ren'Py is the FIRST language whose programs are
# fundamentally STORIES with branching narrative — not algorithms,
# data transformations, or computational tasks.
#
# Ren'Py is also the FIRST documented GAME-DEVELOPMENT-DOMAIN
# language.  The closest existing analogs in the taxonomy:
#   * Wuffs R537 — parser DSL (file formats)
#   * Move R??? — smart-contract DSL
#   * Cairo R??? — ZK-proof DSL
#   * Logtalk R533 — OO logic programming
#   * Modelica R529 — physical-system modeling
# None of these target interactive narrative.  Ren'Py is uniquely
# positioned as the "scripting language for visual novels."
